process.name: Test Queue actions on invalid queues

stage.name: Add To Queue
stage.narrative:
The Data collection contains the items to be added to the queue. The collection may contain single or multiple rows, with each representing an item to be added.
If there is a failure during the process, the queue will be unchanged - i.e. no rows will be loaded even if the error occurred on the last one.
If Defer Until is specified, the items will not be available to be worked until then. Otherwise, they are available immediately.
If the queue has a key field defined, an item added has key data longer than the maximum permitted 255 characters, an error will occur

input.name: Queue Name
input.narrative: The name of the queue to add items to
input.expr: "This isn't a queue name and never will be."

input.name: Data
input.narrative: A collection containing the data, one row for each item to be added

input.name: Defer Until
input.narrative: Optionally, the date/time the new item(s) should be deferred until

input.name: Priority
input.narrative: Optionally, the priority for the new item(s). Lower numbers represent higher priorities. The default is 0.

input.name: Tags
input.narrative: Optionally, a semi-colon-separated set of tags to apply to the queue item(s)

input.name: Status
input.narrative: Optionally, the initial status required of the work queue item(s)

output.name: Item IDs
output.narrative: The IDs of the items which have been added to the queue, in the order of the collection of data passed that was input

exception.detail: "The action 'Add to Queue' passed when it should have failed."

decision.expression: [Exception]="The queue with name 'This isn't a queue name and never will be.' was not found"

exception.detail: "This is not the error message you were expecting: "&[Exception]

stage.name: Get Pending Items
stage.narrative: Retrieves the IDs for all currently pending work queue items in the specified queue, matching the given tags

input.name: Queue Name
input.narrative: The name of the queue for which the pending items are required
input.expr: "This isn't a queue name and never will be."

input.name: Key Filter
input.narrative: Optionally, a key value to filter by. Only items with this key value will be considered.

input.name: Tag Filter
input.narrative: Optionally, a tag mask to filter by. This can consist of any number of tag searches - each term can be separated by a semi-colon and they are all applied to the search (ie. they are AND'ed terms not OR'ed terms). For example, "Account: Joint; -Balance: Overdrawn; Card: *Visa*" will include any items which match all the terms, ie. every item must have an 'Account: Joint' tag applied, no item can have a 'Balance: Overdrawn' tag applied, every item must have a tag applied which starts with 'Card: ' and then contains the text 'Visa'.

input.name: Maximum
input.narrative: Optionally, the maximum number of items to return. Default is to return all items

input.name: Skip
input.narrative: Optionally, the number of items to skip before returning. Default is zero, ie. return all items from the head of the queue

output.name: Pending Items
output.narrative: The currently pending items in the queue, referenced by ID. The single column is 'Item ID' : text. The elements in the collection will be in the order in which they will be loaded by the 'Get Next Item' action.

decision.expression: [Exception]="The queue with name 'This isn't a queue name and never will be.' was not found"

stage.name: Delete Processes Items
stage.narrative:
The Data collection contains the items to be added to the queue. The collection may contain single or multiple rows, with each representing an item to be added.
If there is a failure during the process, the queue will be unchanged - i.e. no rows will be loaded even if the error occurred on the last one.
If Defer Until is specified, the items will not be available to be worked until then. Otherwise, they are available immediately.
If the queue has a key field defined, an item added has key data longer than the maximum permitted 255 characters, an error will occur

input.name: Queue Name
input.narrative: The name of the queue to delete items from
input.expr: "This isn't a queue name and never will be."

input.name: Date Threshold
input.narrative: The threshold date. Items completed or marked with an exception before this date will be deleted from the queue - if not given, all processed items in the specified queue will be deleted.

input.name: Delete From All Queues
input.narrative: Indicates whether to delete items from all queues. If this flag is set to true you cannot specify a queue to delete from. This value defaults to false if nothing is entered.

output.name: Deletion Count
output.narrative: Indicates the number of items which were deleted (which may legitimately be zero).

decision.expression: [Exception]="The queue with name 'This isn't a queue name and never will be.' was not found"

stage.name: Get Completed Items
stage.narrative: Gets the work items from the specified queue which have been marked as complete

input.name: Queue Name
input.narrative: The name of the queue to retrieve the completed items from
input.expr: "This isn't a queue name and never will be."

input.name: Start Date
input.narrative: The start date from which any items marked as complete should be returned. Optional - No date indicates no start date threshold

input.name: End Date
input.narrative: The end date up to which any items marked as complete should be returned. Optional - No date indicates no end date threshold

input.name: Key Filter
input.narrative: Optionally, a key value to filter by. Only items with this key value will be considered.

input.name: Tag Filter
input.narrative: Optionally, a tag mask to filter by. This can consist of any number of tag searches - each term can be separated by a semi-colon and they are all applied to the search (ie. they are AND'ed terms not OR'ed terms). For example, "Account: Joint; -Balance: Overdrawn; Card: *Visa*" will include any items which match all the terms, ie. every item must have an 'Account: Joint' tag applied, no item can have a 'Balance: Overdrawn' tag applied, every item must have a tag applied which starts with 'Card: ' and then contains the text 'Visa'.

input.name: Maximum Rows
input.narrative: The maximum number of rows to return. Optional - No value indicates that all rows should be returned

output.name: Completed Items
output.narrative: The items which were marked as complete within the given date range, up to the maximum count if one was given

decision.expression: [Exception]="The queue with name 'This isn't a queue name and never will be.' was not found"

stage.name: Get Locked Items
stage.narrative: Retrieves the IDs and locked times for all currently locked work queue items in the specified queue, matching the given tags

input.name: Queue Name
input.narrative: The name of the queue for which the locked items are required
input.expr: "This isn't a queue name and never will be."

input.name: Key Filter
input.narrative: Optionally, a key value to filter by. Only items with this key value will be considered.

input.name: Tags
input.narrative: Optionally, a tag mask to filter by. This can consist of any number of tag searches - each term can be separated by a semi-colon and they are all applied to the search (ie. they are AND'ed terms not OR'ed terms). For example, "Account: Joint; -Balance: Overdrawn; Card: *Visa*" will include any items which match all the terms, ie. every item must have an 'Account: Joint' tag applied, no item can have a 'Balance: Overdrawn' tag applied, every item must have a tag applied which starts with 'Card: ' and then contains the text 'Visa'.

output.name: Locked Items
output.narrative: The currently locked items in the queue. Columns are 'Item ID' : text, and 'Locked' : datetime. The elements in the collection will be in locked date/time order

decision.expression: [Exception]="The queue with name 'This isn't a queue name and never will be.' was not found"

stage.name: Get Next Item
stage.narrative:
This action gets the next item to be worked from the queue, returning its details and locking it so no other case can work it.
Items with higher priorities (lower numerical value) are processed first. Where the priority is the same, the next item is the one that has been in the queue the longest, is not already locked, and is not already completed.
The Item ID returned is used to make further calls to update the work status for that item. It may be empty, in which case there are no items available. This can mean either a) the queue is empty, or b) the queue is not running. This mechanism can be used to cleanly stop all processes working a particular queue at the end of the next case. Items that have a 'deferred' time set will not be returned unless that time has been reached.

input.name: Queue Name
input.narrative: The name of the queue
input.expr: "This isn't a queue name and never will be."

input.name: Key Filter
input.narrative: Optionally, a key value to filter by. Only items with this key value will be considered.

input.name: Tag Filter
input.narrative: Optionally, a tag mask to filter by. This can consist of any number of tag searches - each term can be separated by a semi-colon and they are all applied to the search (ie. they are AND'ed terms not OR'ed terms). For example, "Account: Joint; -Balance: Overdrawn; Card: *Visa*" will include any items which match all the terms, ie. every item must have an 'Account: Joint' tag applied, no item can have a 'Balance: Overdrawn' tag applied, every item must have a tag applied which starts with 'Card: ' and then contains the text 'Visa'.

output.name: Item ID
output.narrative: The ID of the item retrieved - empty if there are none available.

output.name: Data
output.narrative: The data associated with the item - a single collection row.

output.name: Attempts
output.narrative: The number of attempts already made to work this item.

decision.expression: [Exception]="The queue with name 'This isn't a queue name and never will be.' was not found"

stage.name: Get Report Data
stage.narrative: Retrieves queue data for analysis. The queue name and at least one of the date parameters must be provided when calling this action

input.name: Queue Name
input.narrative: The name of the queue for which the details are required. This parameter is mandatory
input.expr: "This isn't a queue name and never will be."

input.name: Finished Start Date
input.narrative: The item finish (complete or exception) date/time to start results

input.name: Finished End Date
input.narrative: The item finish (complete or exception) date/time to end results. If empty, this is the end of the day from the start date/time or ignored if the 'finished start date' isn't set

input.name: Loaded Start Date
input.narrative: The item loaded (added to queue) date/time to start results. If empty, then the loaded start date is ignored

input.name: Loaded End Date
input.narrative: The item loaded (added to queue) date/time to end results. If empty, this is the end of the day from the loaded start date/time. If that is also empty, then this parameter is ignored

input.name: Resource Names
input.narrative: The semi-colon-separated names of the resources which worked the item. If empty, this will retrieve for all resources

input.name: Tags
input.narrative: Optionally, a tag mask to filter by. This can consist of any number of tag searches - each term can be separated by a semi-colon and they are all applied to the search (ie. they are AND'ed terms not OR'ed terms). For example, "Account: Joint; -Balance: Overdrawn; Card: *Visa*" will include any items which match all the terms, ie. every item must have an 'Account: Joint' tag applied, no item can have a 'Balance: Overdrawn' tag applied, every item must have a tag applied which starts with 'Card: ' and then contains the text 'Visa'.

input.name: Include unworked items?
input.narrative: Include any items which are currently pending - default is False

input.name: Include deferred items?
input.narrative: Include any items which are currently deferred - default is False

input.name: Include completed items?
input.narrative: Include any items which are currently completed - default is False

input.name: Include exception items?
input.narrative: Include any items which are currently exceptioned - default is False

input.name: Treat each attempt separately?
input.narrative: Each time a queue item exceptions, a new linked 'retry' item is created with an incremented attempt number. By default, all attempts for an item will be treated as a single item for the purposes of the report. An argument of 'True' will indicate that each retry should be treated as a separate item.

output.name: Item Count
output.narrative: The total number of queue items matched with the given parameters

output.name: Time Total
output.narrative: The total amount of time spent working with the matched queue items

output.name: Least Time
output.narrative: The least amount of time spent working on a single matched queue item

output.name: Most Time
output.narrative: The most amount of time spent working on a single matched queue item

output.name: Median Time
output.narrative: The median amount of time spent by the matched queue items

output.name: Mean Time
output.narrative: The mean amount of time spent by each matched queue item

output.name: Item IDs
output.narrative: The Item IDs of all work queue items matched by the search. Note that all attempts of the same item have the same Item ID, and each attempt's ID will appear in this collection at most once, regardless of the 'Treat each attempt separately?' parameter

decision.expression: [Exception]="Error retrieving data: The queue with name 'This isn't a queue name and never will be.' was not found"

stage.name: Is Item in Queue
stage.narrative: Check if an item with the given key is already in the queue

input.name: Queue Name
input.narrative: The name of the queue to check
input.expr: "This isn't a queue name and never will be."

input.name: Key
input.narrative: The key to check.

input.name: Include Pending
input.narrative: Check any items in the queue which are currently awaiting being worked. This will include any deferred items which have a deferral date in the past and any locked items. Optional - Default is True

input.name: Include Deferred
input.narrative: Check any items in the queue which are currently deferred to a later date. Optional - Default is True

input.name: Include Completed
input.narrative: Check any items in the queue which are completed. Optional - Default is True

input.name: Include Terminated
input.narrative: Check any items in the queue which have been fully terminated. Optional - Default is True

output.name: Result
output.narrative: True if an item with the given key is in the queue, False otherwise.

output.name: Item IDs
output.narrative: The Item IDs which represent the work items found with the given key
